    "Hours Today" : "Timer i dag",
    "Hours at a glance" : "Timer p\u00e5 et blik",
    "Hours of rest between end of work and next start. German law requires at least 11 hours." : "Hviletimer mellem arbejdets afslutning og n\u00e6ste start. Tysk lov krever mindst 11 timer.",
    "Hours paid" : "Timer betalt",
    "How Long to Keep Time Records" : "Hvor l\u00e6nge skal man opbevare tidsregistreringer",
    "How Serious" : "Hvor seri\u00f8st",
    "How it works" : "Hvordan det virker",
    "How many hours of rest someone must have between the end of one work day and the start of the next. German law requires at least 11 hours. Example: If someone finishes work at 6 PM, they cannot start again before 5 AM the next day." : "Hvor mange timers hvile en person skal ha mellem slutningen av \u200b\u200ben arbeidsdag og starten av \u200b\u200bden n\u00e6ste. Tysk lov krever mindst 11 timer. Eksempel: Hvis noen afslutter arbeidet kl. 18.00, kan de ikke starte igen f\u00f8r kl. 05.00 n\u00e6ste dag.",
    "How many hours you normally work each day. Decimal values are allowed (e.g. 7.74 for a 38.7 h week spread over five days)." : "Hvor mange timer jobber du normalt hver dag. Decimalv\u00e6rdier er tillatt (f.eks. 7,74 for en uke p\u00e5 38,7 timer fordelt p\u00e5 fem dager).",
    "How many vacation days you get each year. In Germany, the standard is 25 days. Example: Enter 25 if you get 25 vacation days per year." : "Hvor mange feriedager f\u00e5r du hvert \u00e5r. I Tyskland er standarden 25 dager. Eksempel: Skriv inn 25, hvis du f\u00e5r 25 feriedager om \u00e5ret.",
    "How many years to keep time tracking records before they are automatically deleted. German law typically requires keeping records for 2 years. Example: Enter 2 to keep records for 2 years." : "Hvor mange \u00e5r skal man opbevare tidsregistreringer, f\u00f8r de automatisk slettes. Tysk lov krever typisk journalf\u00f8ring i 2 \u00e5r. Eksempel: Skriv inn 2 for at opbevare optegnelser i 2 \u00e5r.",
    "How should annual vacation be calculated?" : "Hvordan skal den \u00e5rlige ferie beregnes?",
    "How the system checked each layer" : "Hvordan systemet kontrollerede hvert lag",
    "How time zones are used" : "Hvordan tidszoner bruges",
    "How times are stored" : "Hvordan tider lagremes",
    "How vacation days are calculated" : "Slik beregnes feriedager",
    "How well you follow the rules:" : "Hvor godt f\u00f8lger du reglerne:",
    "How your request is approved" : "Hvordan din foresp\u00f8rsel godkjennes",
    "How your vacation entitlement is calculated" : "Slik beregnes din ferieret",
    "Hypothetical team" : "Hypotetisk team",
    "Hypothetical team membership" : "Hypotetisk teammedlemskab",
    "I returned early" : "Jeg kom tidligt tilbake",
    "I understand this action cannot be undone" : "Jeg forst\u00e5r, at denne handling ikke kan fortrydes",
    "If a break is left open for too long, the system automatically clocks out to prevent permanent pause status." : "Hvis en pause st\u00e5r \u00e5ben for l\u00e6nge, stemper systemet automatisk ud for at undg\u00e5 permanent pausestatus.",
    "If a calendar month was finalized by mistake or a correction is required, you can reopen it here as an administrator for the employee whose month should be opened again. Use the search field to select that person (their Nextcloud account). You must enter a reason; the audit log records your administrator action, the reason, and who the change applies to. Previous snapshot rows remain in the database for traceability." : "Hvis en kalenderm\u00e5ned er avsluttet ved en feil, eller det er behov for en korrigering, kan du gen\u00e5pnee den her som administrator for den medarbeider, hvis m\u00e5ned skal \u00e5pnees igen. Brug s\u00f8kefeltet til at velge denne person (deres Nextcloud-konto). Du skal indtaste en begrunnelse; revisionsloggen registrerer din administratorhandling, begrunnelseen og hvem \u00e6ndringen g\u00e6lder for. Tidligere snapshot-r\u00e6kker forblir i databasen for sporbarhed.",
    "If enabled, users can still turn this reminder off in their personal settings. Reminders are sent only for expected workdays (not weekends, holidays, or approved absences)." : "Hvis den er aktivert, kan brukere fortsatt sl\u00e5 denne p\u00e5mindelse fra i deres personlige innstillinger. P\u00e5mindelser sendes kun for forventede arbeidsdager (ikke weekender, helligdager eller godkjent frav\u00e6r).",
    "If enabled: managers are resolved from ArbeitszeitCheck teams defined below. If disabled: managers are resolved from shared Nextcloud groups (default behavior)." : "Hvis aktivert: ledere l\u00f8ses fra ArbeitszeitCheck-team defineret nedenfor. Hvis deaktivert: ledere l\u00f8ses fra delte Nextcloud-grupper (standardadf\u00e6rd).",
    "If set, opening carryover per user cannot exceed this many days (Tarifvertrag / company policy). Leave empty for no cap. Imports and admin edits are clamped to this value." : "Hvis det er settlet, kan \u00e5pneingsoverf\u00f8rsel per bruker ikke overstige s\u00e5 mange dager (Tarifvertrag / organisasjonspolicy). Lad v\u00e6re tom for ingen l\u00e5g. Importer og administratorredigeringer er fastgjort til denne v\u00e6rdi.",
    "If set, this date is saved as the overtime \u201cStichtag\u201d when the new account is created. Leave empty to configure later in ArbeitszeitCheck \u2192 Administration \u2192 Employees." : "Hvis den er angivet, lagremes denne dato som overtidt \"Stichtag\", n\u00e5r den nye konto oppretttes. Lad v\u00e6re tom for at konfigurere senere i ArbeitszeitCheck \u2192 Administrasjon \u2192 Medarbeidere.",
    "If you manage more than one team, you can choose one here." : "Hvis du leder mer end \u00e9t team, kan du velge et her.",
    "If you need help at any time, check the documentation or contact your administrator." : "Hvis du til enhver tid har brug for hj\u00e6lp, kan du sjekkke dokumentationen eller kontakte din administrator.",
    "If you need to generate reports, please contact your administrator or manager." : "Hvis du har brug for at generere rapporter, bedes du kontakte din administrator eller leder.",
    "If you think the result is wrong, please contact your HR administrator." : "Hvis du mener, at resultatet er forkert, bedes du kontakte din HR-administrator.",
    "If you were sick during vacation, please shorten or cancel the vacation first, then submit a separate sick leave request." : "Hvis du har v\u00e6ret syg i ferien, bedes du f\u00f8rst afkorte eller aflyse ferien og derefter sende inn en s\u00e6rskilt sykefrav\u00e6rsforesp\u00f8rsel.",
